---
The Reliquary Host was the martial custodial office of the Gloamvault, one of three interlocked
houses—alongside the Bell Synod and Ash Scriptorium—that governed Kel'Shadra's oath-archive
institution. The Host publicly protected sanctity and guarded relics, prisoners, and ceremonial
remains. Privately, it enforced compliance with institutional decisions through staged accidents,
intimidation, and direct force when other mechanisms failed. The Host's knights were presented
as guardians of sacred objects; their operational function was to make sure contested truths
did not exit the institution with witnesses who could act on them. When the Bell Synod exposed
falsified absolution records during the Night of Unsounded Bells, the Host split: one wing
sided with the reform bloc and attempted to secure the archive stacks; the other wing took
direct command from Synod hardliners and suppressed the reform. This internal fracture is the
origin of the Riven Gate catastrophe—reformist Host members detonated emergency ward pylons
to prevent annihilation, cracking both masonry and institutional doctrine. The Sepulcher Compact,
an autonomous martial sub-body within the Host, buried its knights where they served and
raised them through oath-bonding rites to ensure command continuity beyond death—the origin
of the warden remnants that still operate in Kel'Shadra's deep chambers.

